<br>
Rogg, I understand your reasoning and I can see why you based your conclusions on that reasoning.  But take a moment and look at the history of FCFS mobs.<br>
<br>
As time progresses, mobs appear to be less contested for.  The race for FCFS mobs is now much more relaxed.  People now let others that get to a mob first setup and have an attempt instead of running them over.  For FCFS mobs, teaming up is not unheard of, yet it's not a big deal.  If AD follows history, I feel that it will go the way of the Luclin FCFS mobs and become less contested and eventually no one will care if people team up for it or not.<br>
<br>
If AD is made a rotation, it should be made a RTA rotation for being a highly contested mob now, not for what may or may not occur in the future.  In the future, if AD is a non RTA rotaton mob and becomes like a Sev rotation because of all the teaming, then make it a RTA rotation mob.  In the future, if AD is a RTA rotation mob but there is verly little competition, then drop the rotation.  But to make AD a RTA rotation or not should be based on what is going on now.<br>
<br>
Right now, there has only been one heard instance of teaming up on AD even though all guilds currently have the oppurtunity to team up on it.  So we can safely conclude that the teaming up on AD that is occuring now isn't causing a Sev like non RTA rotation.  The guilds killing AD now need to ask themselves if there is a lot of competition amongst themselves, and then make a decision based on that.<br>
<br>
I would also like to point out that the reason why AD isn't a RTA rotation now is becuase most guilds have moved on after getting flagged.  In fact, a lot of guilds like Fires of Heaven and BoTS have complained that until Rallos Zek the Warlord, the loot on flagging mobs wasn't worth their while.  Whether this trend continues really depends on the route the individual guilds choose to take.<br>
<br>
But it goes to show that there wasn't a need to make AD a rotation when our server's upper progressed guilds were killing AD so no rotation exists.  The upper middle progressed guilds killing AD now need to ask themselves if they are going to continue killing AD after they get flagged and is there a lot of competition for AD now.  If so, make AD a rotation, if not, leave it alone.  In the future, we can re-examine this and ask if AD needs to be made or remain a rotation or not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dembiredeadbones>Dembire Deadbones</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.w3.org/Icons/Misc/skeleton.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/21/03 10:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=406>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> Very good post Rogg!! You answered my question and was very articulate. (I don't mean the eat me part hehe)<br>
