<br>
<br>
I have done the alternate quest, which by the way is no longer working (hopefully fixed by patch going on as I type), to enter HoH and CoD.  I rarely fight there for XP (only once in a group and a few times soloing).  HoH-b is out of reach, off limits, beyond my grasp and practically non existent.  I have worked harder than 90% of the other people who have access to this zone by accomplishing the quest.  My reward is less content.  Those that just happen to be in a nice big fat guild and threw a few nukes/heals/backstabs/kicks/dots in at the appropriate time for a ten minute period are rewarded with more content and the opportunity to advance farther into the elemental planes.  Those of us who alt quested to enter tier three zones do NOT have that opportunity, although we deserve it!  That is the main issue at stake here.  The guilds who have been able to gather enough forces to take down AD get the chance to go to other planes beyond HoH.  By suggesting that we &quot;do the alternate quest if you want into HoH&quot; you suggest also that we limit our opportunity for advancement.  This may seem fair and upright to you who are already there, but to the rest of us it seems like you are blocking a path.<br>
<br>
As far as punishment for teaming goes... if a single guild has followed the rules on doing rotation mobs w/o help and has continued to hold to those conventions on past conquests they should never lose those rights.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I believe that restrictions (ie; permanent/temporary alliances) should only be placed on mobs that were teamed on and any content that is beyond that encounter.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  So say FK and ED teamed on AD to get HoH flags.  Until such time as they are able to do this encounter solo they should be forced to share any rotations beyond HoH.  To take away all the hard work and dedication that these seperate entities have put forth before this teaming event is completely absurd.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Soneya<br>
I find it odd that someone wants all the protection but none of the restrictions. IE when BotS, Tindi, NB get done raiding at 8-10pm at night, 2 or 3 groups from any one guild don't go around looking to gank old expasions Rotation mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Let me tackle this reoccurring thought from you here hun... have you ever heard of people forming pick up groups to take down named Giants in PoS in order to get their BoT keys?<br>
<br>
Well it goes like this... players, some guilded some not, get together and form a raid of players (from several different guilds usually) to run around PoS and &quot;gank&quot; named giants.  It happens often.  Almost every day.  The medallions that these giants drop are worth a great deal, as they provide access to something every player who reaches 65th level will want.  Glyphed runes!  We all need them and want them and cannot have them unless we can access a tier three zone.  Practically all of these spells are worth as much or more than any loot dropped by old world rotation mobs.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Why is this an accepted practice but teaming to take down AD/Grummus/Behemoth is not condoned?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  After all... BoT also provides access to a boss mob that leads the way to a higher level plane.  <br>
<br>
This is the type of inconsistency I and many others see.  It is also why I believe the larger guilds are using the &quot;spirit of the Rathe&quot; and it's rotation rules to &quot;gank&quot; the better content for themselves for as long as they possibly can, maybe for all time.  The fact is that smaller guilds will NEVER be able to reach certain areas on their own no matter how powerful their members become unless they are allowed to team up.  You know this all to well and have rules that will penalize these players who are already at a distinct disadvantage.  Yes these rules were set up to make things more fair for everyone, however they seem to only be shouted from the mountain tops when it suits the purposes of those who are making the rules.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
<br>
Happy patch day everyone : )~ <p><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Always Pursuing The Chase</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=455992"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-size:medium;"> PSLEESTAK</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
